obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3511)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "except the State of Hyderabad" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3511&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Cadet Corps`
  line `Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends, to the whole of India ^1* * * and applies to all persons enrolled or appointed under this`
  line `Act, wherever they may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3512)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3512&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `"corps" means the National Cadet Corps constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `"enrolled" means enrolled in the Corps under this Act;`
  line
  line `"prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `"school" includes any institution recognised in this behalf by the Central Government or the State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `"university" means any university established by law in India and includes colleges affiliated to`
  line `universities, intermediate colleges and such technical institutions of collegiate status, as are`
  line `recognised in this behalf by the Central Government or the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3513)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the National Cadet Corps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3513&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `There shall be raised and maintained in the manner`
  line `hereinafter provided a Corps, to be designated the National Cadet Corps:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may establish all or any of the units of the Corps as and when`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3514)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution and disbandment of units.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or Acceding State" omitted by A.O. 1950 (w.e.f. 26-1-1950).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3514&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may constitute in any State`
  line `^1* * * one or more units of the Corps members of which shall be recruited from amongst the students of`
  line `any university or school, and may disband or reconstitute any unit so constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3515)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Division of the Corps into Divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3515&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `There shall be three Divisions of the Corps, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Senior Division, recruitment to which shall be from amongst the students of the male sex`
  line `of any university;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Junior Division, recruitment to which shall be from amongst the students of the male sex`
  line `of any school; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the Junior Division, recruitment to which shall be from amongst the students of the female`
  line `sex of any university or school.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3516)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Enrolment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3516&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any student of the male sex of any university may offer himself for enrolment as`
  line `a cadet in the Senior Division, and any student of the male sex of any school may offer himself for`
  line `enrolment as a cadet in the Junior Division if he is of the prescribed age or over.`
  line
  line `(2) Any student of the female sex of any University or school may offer herself for enrolment as a`
  line `cadet in the Girls Division :`
  line
  line `Provided that in the latter case she is of the prescribed age or over.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3517)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Central Government may raise other units.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3517&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, provide for the constitution of any other units of the Corps`
  line `in any place and prescribe the persons or class of persons who may be eligible for enrolment therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3518)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Discharge.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3518&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every person enrolled under this Act shall be entitled to receive his or her discharge`
  line `from the Corps on the expiration of the period for which he or she was enrolled or on his or her ceasing to`
  line `be borne on the roll of the university or school to which he or she may belong:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person enrolled may be discharged at any time by such authority and subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3519)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appointment of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3519&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may provide for the appointment of officers`
  line `in or for any unit of the Corps either from amongst members of the staff of any university or school or`
  line `otherwise and may prescribe the duties, powers and functions of such officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3520)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duties of persons subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3520&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No person subject to this Act shall by virtue of being a`
  line `member of the Corps be liable for active military service, but subject thereto any such person shall be`
  line `liable to perform such duties and discharge such obligations as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3521)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Punishment for offences under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3521&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any person enrolled under this Act may be punished`
  line `for the contravention of any rule made under this Act with fine which may extend to fifty rupees to be`
  line `recovered in such manner and by such authority as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3522)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to appoint Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3522&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may for the purpose of`
  line `advising it on all matters of policy connected with the constitution and administration of the Corps`
  line `appoint a Central Advisory Committee consisting of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister for Defence, who shall be the Chairman of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Defence, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India, Ministry of Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Financial Advisor, Defence, ex officio;`
  line
  line `^1[(e) the Chief of the Army Staff, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Chief of the Naval Staff, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) the Chief of the Air Staff, ex officio;]`
  line
  line `(h) five non-official members to be nominated by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `^2[(i) three Members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People and`
  line `one by the Council of States.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) A member elected under clause (i) of sub-section (1) shall hold office for a period of one`
  line `year from the date of his election or until he ceases to be a Member of the House which elected him,`
  line `whichever is earlier.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may also appoint, for the same purpose as is specified in sub-section (1),`
  line `such ^4* * * State Advisory Committees as it may consider desirable from time to time and may prescribe`
  line `their duties and functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for clauses (e), (f) and (g).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 50 of 1975, s. 2, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 16-8-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 50 of 1975, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-8-1975).`
  line
  line `4. The words "Provincial or" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3523)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178&sectionId=3523&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00014_194831_1517807324178
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules to carry out the objects of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribe the conditions subject to which universities or schools shall be allowed to raise units`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the persons or class of persons who may be eligible for enrolment under section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the manner in which, the period for which and the conditions subject to which any`
  line `person or class of persons may be enrolled under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) provide for the medical examination of persons offering themselves for enrolment under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe preliminary and periodical military training for any person or class of persons`
  line `subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribe the military or other obligations to which members of the Corps shall be liable when`
  line `undergoing military training and provide generally for the maintenance of discipline amongst`
  line `members of the Corps;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribe the duties, powers and functions of officers appointed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) prescribe the allowances or other remuneration payable to persons subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) provide for the removal or discharge of any person subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribe the offences for which any person subject to this Act may be tried and provide for`
  line `the trial thereof;`
  line
  line `(k) prescribe the manner in which fines levied under this Act may be recovered;`
  line
  line `(l) prescribe the duties, powers and functions of Central ^1* * * or State Advisory Committees; and`
  line
  line `(m) provide for any other matter which under this Act is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "Provincial" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 50 of 1975, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-8-1975).`
